:stubs out half smoked cigarette into overflowing ashtray: <br>
Its been two days since I tried to fix the phone jack in the wall, perhaps I should have given up instead of jerking it out of the wall in frustration...but hindsite is 20/20.  Vampire the Masquerade isn't working well as a crutch.  I don't feel I am uber dressed in rags and carrying a sword and sheild.  The lootz while not phat, are easy to get...they lay in piles on the floor.<br>
:relites another half smoked one:<br>
So far I have only killed a few low level vampires, and apparently when I used to play the table top version we did disciplines wrong, because we thought Fortitude gave you extra chances to soak damage and each vampire I have slain that uses it before the battle drops in one hit vs the many it takes to slay the ones not using it.  I am still not used to leaving my enemies' bodies on the floor without sorting thru the mush, looking for change.  <br>
:cocks head to the side, reasonably sure I can hear my monk crying from somewhere in the distance:<br>
Free will isn't apparent in this dank and drab world, I chose no stats or classes, although no one asks for my change or rags when I stand inside the city gates.  MY KINGDOM FOR A NEWBIE BEGGAR!!!<br>
<br>
